This paper is about multi-agent learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper focuses on game theory and convergence guarantees, which are topics typically studied in the cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The use of gradient-based learning algorithms suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on convergence in dynamic environments suggests that it may also be relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), followed by cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.SY.
